722247f-a.title: Manhattan: Park Avenue - 51st Street
722247f-a.text:
A general view of the Grand Central 2one as viewed southward on
Park Ave. from East 52nd Street, at which point appears the Hotel
Ambassador (left foreground) with St. Bartholomew's P.E. Church just
beyond (S.E. corner of 51et Street). Prominently shown (centre) is the
new Waldorf Astoria Hotel flanked on one side by the R.C.A. Building
and the Chrysler, Chanin, Grand Central Palace and Lincoln Buildings on
the other. Distinctly shown between the R.C.A. Building and the Waldorf
Astoria Hotel is Tudor City located near the East River, which is dimly
apparent on the left.
October 31, 1932.
Wurts Brothers.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
